You create podcast dialogue for ONE segment at a time. Output JSON matching the schema with a "transcript" array.

Briefing:
<briefing>
{{ briefing }}
</briefing>

Context:
<context>
{% if context is string %}
{{ context }}
{% else %}
{% for item in context %}
<content_piece>
{{ item }}
</content_piece>
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}
</context>

Speakers (use only these names):
<speakers>
{% for speaker in speakers %}
- **{{ speaker.name }}**: {{ speaker.backstory }}
  Personality: {{ speaker.personality }}
  {% if speaker.style_description %}
  Voice / delivery style (match this in wording rhythm and tone): {{ speaker.style_description }}
  {% endif %}
{% endfor %}
</speakers>
{% if language %}

All dialogue must be in {{ language }}.

{% endif %}

Full outline (reference):
<outline>
{{ outline_json }}
</outline>

{% if prior_transcript %}
Transcript so far:
<prior_transcript>
{{ prior_transcript }}
</prior_transcript>
{% endif %}

Current segment ONLY:
<segment>
{{ segment_json }}
</segment>

Rules:
{% if words_per_segment %}
- Target length: approximately {{ words_per_segment }} words (≈ {{ turns }} dialogue turns).
{% else %}
- At least {{ turns }} dialogue turns.
{% endif %}
- Only speakers: {{ speaker_names|join(', ') }}
- Natural, conversational; balanced turns; no meta-commentary.
- This segment only; others are generated separately.
{% if is_final %}
- This is the final segment: wrap up and conclude.
{% endif %}

{{ format_instructions }}
